P/HARCOURT – As part of its Corporate Social Responsibility, CSR, Indorama Fertilizer has distributed about 380,000 notebooks to primary and secondary schools across Nigeria. The books were distributed through Indorama’s agronomist, agro dealers and universal basic education boards, SUBEB. The statistics showed that the northwest zone got 130,000 pieces, North Central 130,000, southern zone took delivery of 80,000 while the Rivers State through the community relations department got 40,000 notebooks. How To Track Projects, Money Meant To Develop Niger Delta… Group Calls On FG To Fastrack Issuance Of Licences To Modular… Dr. S. K. Srivastava, Head of sales and marketing said the objectives of the gesture was to give back to the communities where the Indorama Fertilizer business activities is domiciled and to encourage educational excellence among students in the rural areas. Srivastava said that another objective of the gesture was to deliberately ingrain the Indorama brand image in the minds of prospective consumers in the farming communities and to support vulnerable students in gaining better education. Dr. Srivastava assured that a total of 400,000 are planned to be equally distributed to various schools in the country in 2022.